name: kennard-stone
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "kennard-stone" %}
{% set dirname = "kennard_stone" %}
{% set version = "1.1.2" %}

package:
  name: "{{ name|lower }}"
  version: "{{ version }}"

source:
  url: "https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ dirname }}/{{ dirname }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz"
  sha256: c7e411ff7e4df35b652343a36e1d502f730933312085eb2fbb271f288124d872

build:
  noarch: python
  number: 0
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv"

requirements:
  host:
    - pip
    - python >=3.6
  run:
    - numpy
    - pandas
    - python >=3.6
    - scikit-learn

test:
  imports:
    - kennard_stone

about:
  home: "https://github.com/yu9824/kennard_stone"
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE 
  summary: "A method for selecting samples by spreading the training data evenly."
  dev_url: "https://github.com/yu9824/{{ dirname }}/"

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - yu9824
